<![CDATA[ <figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*PVh-57wceNkz2t63CrNd2w.jpeg" /></figure><p>Values and fundamentals are better than just technical skills. Technical content will change and will be improved. The code that we write today is very different than decades ago. Although, values may last forever.</p><p>After many years working in this area and with different people around the world, I strongly believe that the best values that you could have as a Software Engineer are the following.</p><h3>Quality First</h3><p>You always try to write the best code. Going well is going faster!</p><h3>Adaptability</h3><p>You are not attached to a framework, specific language, or just one project. You easily adapt to new environments.</p><h3>Communication</h3><p>You have clear and objective written and verbal communication, especially in your code.</p><h3>Growth mindset</h3><p>You should know which are the next steps to improve as a Software Engineer and you are always learning.</p><h3>Testability</h3><p>You don‚Äôt trust in your ability to test all things. You automate this process.</p><h3>Humanity</h3><p>You treat others with respect and humanity.</p><h3>Mentoring</h3><p>You can teach others. When you teach, you learn more.</p><h3>Conclusion</h3><p>The main idea of this post is to be simple, just to help you to remind which values you should be aware of as a Software Engineer and get to the next level.</p><img src="https://medium.com/_/stat?event=post.clientViewed&referrerSource=full_rss&postId=12a312a9a411" width="1" height="1" alt=""> ]]>
